'''Assad John Haloute''' is the founder and executive director of the [[Chefette]] fast food chain in [[Barbados]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.broadstreetjournalbarbados.com/business-briefs/2010-08-07/haloute-chefette-foreign-franchising-%E2%80%9Csometime-in-this-generation%E2%80%9D|title=Haloute: Chefette foreign franchising "sometime in this generation"|last=Hoyos|first=Patrick|date=7 August 2010|work=Broad Street Journal|accessdate=2 April 2011}}</ref> He was born in San Fernando, Trinidad and is of [[Demographics of Syria|Syrian]] origin. Chefette Restaurants was founded in 1972 and has grown into 15 outlets islandwide: 10 drive-thrus, 8 playgrounds, and 2 Barbecue Barns (fast casual dining).

